climbs.name: Saturn V
climbs.fa: Dylan Pike and Case Turner, July 2019

content.description:
Identify a lightly vegetated corner with another left facing corner approximately 5' to the right. Stem up the rightmost corner, placing gear behind a flake on the right wall. Layback up a finger crack, then climb into the wide crack above. Rest below the first roof, then pull it on 4 C4 sized jams. Climb the hand and fist crack above to a second roof. Turn the roof to the left and clip the bolts.

Lower off two stainless bolts with a 70 m rope. A 60 might make it if you're willing to downclimb the easy terrain at the start of the route.
content.location: Saturn V is located roughly in the center of the west half of Rocket Ridge. The route climbs a left facing corner with two roofs, one at mid height, and one at approximately 30m.
